  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6594.79 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-12.5B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+15.2B), dealers are currently in amplification mode and likely buying this level as spot hovers near multiple negative gamma strikes. The breakout regime with -14.3B total GEX means dealers will continue to chase momentum - buying rallies toward 6605 where they'll flip to selling pressure, and aggressively buying any dips back toward the 6580-6590 cluster of negative gamma. Watch for explosive moves if we break either 6605 (dealers turn into sellers) or fall below 6580 (dealers buy more aggressively into weakness).\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile swings with strong dealer buying support around 6590 but selling pressure if we push above 6605.",
